Note that using A.this.type instead of this_a.type doesn't help -- same behaviour.

A general workaround requires passing this_a.type as a type parameter:
```scala
scala> class A {
     |   this_a =>
     |   def b= new B[this_a.type]
     |   class B[E >: this_a.type] {
     |     def a: E= this_a
     |   }
     | }
defined class A

scala> def a= new A {
     |   def c { }
     | }
a: A{def c: Unit}

scala> a.b.a.c

scala> 
```
